Next.js 15 mein latest routing components likhne ke liye yahan kuch tareeke aur example code diye gaye hain:

**1. Client-Side Routing ke liye `Link` Component ka use karein:**
`next/link` se `Link` component ka use karke aap pages ke beech navigate kar sakte hain.

```tsx
import Link from 'next/link'

export default function Page() {
  return <Link href="/dashboard">Dashboard</Link>
}
```

**2. Parallel Routes ke liye Layout Component define karein:**
Jab aapko ek hi layout mein kai sections (jaise dashboard par) simultaneously render karne hon, to parallel routes ka use karein.

```tsx
export default function Layout({
  children,
  team,
  analytics,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode
  analytics: React.ReactNode
  team: React.ReactNode
}) {
  return (
    <>
      {children}
      {team}
      {analytics}
    </>
  )
}
```

**3. Basic Layout Component define karein:**
Ek basic layout component banane ke liye `layout.tsx` ya `layout.js` file ka use karein jo `children` prop ko wrap karta hai.

```tsx
export default function DashboardLayout({
  children,
}: {
  children: React.ReactNode
}) {
  return <section>{children}</section>
}
```

**4. Dynamic Route Parameters ke saath Next.js Page Component:**
Jab aapko URLs mein dynamic segments (jaise `/posts/[slug]`) chahiye hon, to dynamic routes ka use karein. `params` object mein dynamic values milti hain.

```tsx
export default async function Page({
  params,
}: {
  params: Promise<{ slug: string }>
}) {
  return <h1>My Page</h1>
}
```

**5. `useSelectedLayoutSegments` Hook ka use karein (Client Component mein):**
`next/navigation` se `useSelectedLayoutSegments` hook ka use karke aap currently active route segments ko retrieve kar sakte hain.

```tsx
'use client'

import { useSelectedLayoutSegments } from 'next/navigation'

export default function ExampleClientComponent() {
  const segments = useSelectedLayoutSegments()

  return (
    <ul>
      {segments.map((segment, index) => (
        <li key={index}>{segment}</li>
      ))}
    </ul>
  )
}
```
